Case Based, Theory. 

The paper belongs to the sub-category of Case Based AI because it discusses experience-based reasoning and case-adaptation tasks. It also describes a model-based method for solving non-routine case-adaptation tasks. 

The paper also belongs to the sub-category of Theory because it introduces and discusses the concept of generic teleological mechanisms (GTMs) and their use in case adaptation. It also evaluates the computational feasibility and sufficiency of the method proposed.
